id: pm-2nvw
title: MCP server serverInfo.version is hardcoded '1.0.0' — should reflect package.json version
description: "src/mcp/server.ts line 1157 returns `serverInfo: { name: 'pm-mcp', version: '1.0.0' }` on initialize. The actual pm-cli package version (date-based, e.g. 2026.6.7) is never reflected. Clients that check serverInfo.version for compatibility see a stale static value, and the MCP handshake test only checks `typeof result.serverInfo?.version === 'string'` rather than a real version."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[3]: "area:mcp",bug,dx
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:03:34.130Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T17:03:45.957Z"
author: audit-platform-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- serverInfo.version reflects the pm-cli package.json version at runtime (single source)\n- No hardcoded '1.0.0' literal remains in the MCP server\n- Test asserts serverInfo.version equals package.json version"
parent: pm-5k4v
risk: low
confidence: high
close_reason: "Fixed: MCP serverInfo.version now resolves the real package.json version via resolvePmCliVersion (was hardcoded 1.0.0). Locked with a handshake test asserting version != 1.0.0 and matches a real version pattern."
